1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
We often call any unexplained bump a cyst. But cyst, daana, phinsi, boil, and gilti
can describe very different structures—and different levels of urgency.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Cyst-related concerns affected me personally. I built the tool I wish I had then:
visual, private, and honest about what it can and cannot know.

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:35,000
LumpMap 3D is not a diagnostic tool. It is an anatomy-first educational navigator.
The journey begins with one useful clue: location.

4
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Choose from seventeen body regions through a rotatable 3D body
or searchable accessible list.

5
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Selecting the top of the buttock cleft does not return a diagnosis;
it opens patterns worth learning about.

6
00:00:51,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Across fourteen curated lessons, the atlas changes
from body scale to beneath-the-skin scale.

7
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:10,000
For pilonidal disease, three stages show a normal cleft, a pit and sinus tract, and inflamed disease—
labelled as possible progression, not a prediction.

8
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Comparison mode holds the tissue scale constant, so a pilonidal sinus,
a boil, and an epidermoid cyst can be understood side by side.

9
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:34,000
If a user is not sure where to begin, they can describe what they noticed
in English, Urdu, Roman Urdu, or use guided questions.

10
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:44,000
With a server key, GPT-5.6 normalizes everyday wording
into a strict structured symptom record.

11
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:54,000
It does not diagnose, generate medical content, select matches, or decide urgency.
The no-key demo and guided flow keep the safety experience testable.

12
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:02,000
For this Roman Urdu example, local matching recognizes a recurring painful armpit pattern
and places prompt-appointment guidance before curated comparisons, including HS.

13
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:09,000
The Visit Note contains only user-supplied facts.

14
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Now compare painful perianal swelling with fever. Deterministic local rules
raise same-day urgent guidance and show the exact trigger facts.

15
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:27,000
GPT-5.6 cannot lower that result.

16
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I built LumpMap with Codex and GPT-5.6: the interface, procedural Three.js anatomy,
typed safety rules, accessibility, privacy protections, and fifty-six focused tests.

17
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Every lesson shows sources and review dates, with no accounts, trackers,
photo uploads, or saved health history.

18
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Learn the pattern, not a label.
